<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-07-15T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-07-15T07:00:00-05:00" n="477" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">880.00/7–1547: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-07-15T13:00:00+01:00">July 15,
                                    1947—1 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2799. Further to <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 2556, July 11,
                            and my 2781, July 12,<note n="1" xml:id="d477fn1">Latter not printed; it
                                advised waiting until the end of the Conference of European Economic
                                Cooperation, then in session, as Foreign Minister Bidault was
                                engrossed in it (880.00/7–1247).</note> I have received informal
                            indication from very high <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss>
                            source that a recommendation may shortly be made to Bidault that the
                            French take the initiative in asking us for our views and our help in
                            solving problems in North Africa and Indochina. I can not at present
                            forecast how Bidault will react to the suggestion, but tactically it
                            would be so much better if the initiative were to come from the French
                            that I feel strongly we should hold off for the moment. I should know
                            the answer within a week or ten days.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>